# UI/UX Constraints

## Design Principles
- Clean, demo-ready UI. Avoid clutter.
- Minimal controls: one right-side panel maximum.
- Provide "demo presets" for quick showcase scenarios.

## UI Components
- Right-side panel: collapsible, contains all controls.
- HUD: minimal overlay (FPS, sim time, agent count).
- Hide UI button: one-click toggle for recording (hides all UI).

## Controls Organization
- Time controls: play/pause, time scale, step, seed input.
- Camera controls: preset selector (cinematic, follow, freecam).
- Scenario controls: load/save, reset.
- Swarm controls: behavior toggles, formation presets (later milestones).

## Hotkeys
- `C`: Cycle camera presets.
- `H`: Hide/show UI.
- `Space`: Play/pause.
- `R`: Reset scenario.
- Document hotkeys in UI tooltip or README.

## Demo Mode
- "Demo" button: plays prebuilt scenario sequence.
- Auto-hides UI after 2 seconds.
- Loops or resets at end.
- Optimized for 30-60 second LinkedIn clips.

## Styling
- Dark theme (space aesthetic).
- High contrast for readability.
- Minimal animations (smooth transitions, no distracting effects).
